cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR

This paper presents an algorithm for verifying safety properties of typed higher-order functional programs using interprocedural analysis. The paper discusses the use of abstract domains, predicate abstraction, counterexample-guided refinement, and Craig interpolation, which are all techniques commonly used in program analysis and verification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.PL (Programming Languages), followed by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of abstract interpretation, which falls under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), and the verification of safety properties, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
